Statically typed vs. Dynamically typed languages

Type checking is to ensure the program is type-safe, to minimise the possibility of type-errors.

The differences betweeen Statically-typed and Dynamically-typed languages are mentioned below,

	     Statically typed 				    Dynamically typed
		language 		   vs.			language

	1) It performs type checking			1) It performs type checking
	at compile time.				at runtime.

	2) It checks the type of the 			2) It checks the type of the 
	variable before running.			variable while executing.

	3) Eg: Java, C, C++, C#,			3) JavaScript, PHP, Python, Perl, 
	Haskell, Pascal, etc.,				Ruby, Lisp, Groovy, etc.,
	
	
